3. Installing the required MacPorts packages
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Install Xcode 3.0. You can download it from Apple's site after registration (http://developer.apple.com/tools/download).

Install MacPorts (http://www.macports.org/). Then install the following
packages from the Terminal window:

	$ sudo port install glew freetype fribidi libcdio lzo python24 libsdl libsdl_image 
	$ sudo port install libsdl_mixer mysql5-devel pcre samba3 fontconfig libmad portaudio bzip2 jam
	$ sudo port install boost

You will need to use samba3 version 3.0.28a so follow the below instructions to setup MacPorts.

First you can check the version needed by clicking on the button's revision here
http://trac.macports.org/log/trunk/dports/net/samba3/Portfile

We will install the revision 34870 (version 3.0.28a)

Edit /opt/local/etc/macports/sources.conf and add before rsync.macports.org line
"file:///Users/Shared/dports" (without quotes)

	$ sudo mkdir /Users/Shared/dport
	$ cd /Users/Shared/dports
	$ svn co --revision 34870 http://svn.macports.org/repository/macports/trunk/dports/net/samba3 net/samba3
	$ portindex /Users/Shared/dports
	$ port list samba3 (in order to check if the new samba3 is listed)
	$ sudo port uninstall samba3
	$ sudo port install samba3@3.0.28a


If you're having more problems linking due to a versioning of a library, see:
http://journal.bitshaker.com/articles/2007/10/20/install-old-versions-of-ports-using-macports/

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.1 Fix two MacPorts package default install locations with sym links
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
	$ sudo ln -s /opt/local/include/mysql5/mysql/ /opt/local/include/mysql
	$ sudo ln -s /opt/local/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.4/include/python2.4 /opt/local/include/python2.4

